          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">Energy crisis</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/gp-dec-20-2.jpg" alt="Energy crisis" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Iran is in an undesirable <a href="https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2024/12/18/iran-key-services-shut-as-rial-plunges-amid-energy-crisis-regional" target="_blank">situation</a>. It suffers from a significant energy and economic crisis, made worse by regional tensions, harsh winters, and a plummeting currency. Many of Tehran's key services have been shut off. Despite being home to the second-largest natural gas reserve, many problems are due to mismanagement, outdated infrastructure, and international sanctions. These have led to unplanned blackouts, worsened public health, and billions in economic losses.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Iran has dealt with many blows this year. It has engaged with <a href="https://theconversation.com/amid-lull-in-tit-for-tat-missile-exchange-iran-and-israel-seek-to-control-the-online-narrative-242265" target="_blank">Israel</a>, and the downfall of <a href="https://www.npr.org/2024/12/13/nx-s1-5223675/the-collapse-of-the-assad-regime-in-syria-has-been-a-huge-blow-for-iran" target="_blank">Assad</a> has been a geopolitical disaster. Iran also faces a lot of <a href="https://www.dw.com/en/iranians-upset-with-tehran-over-israel-tensions/a-70608764" target="_blank">internal tension</a> and pressure. Many people are dissatisfied with the government for multitudes of reasons; they are tired of the conflict with Israel and dissatisfied with the regime in general. There have been massive protests and opposition that were squashed immediately.  Things are likely to worsen with Donald Trump as president in 2025. His last presidency <a href="https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/6/29/iran-and-us-president-donald-trump-a-timeline-of-key-events" target="_blank">worsened</a> the Iranian-US relations.‚Äã</p>
        </mj-text>
